The paper focuses on the performance of deep neural networks in mobile applications, specifically in terms of inference. This suggests that the paper is likely to fall under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which are commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) applications. The paper also touches on the use of cloud servers for inference, which falls under the distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) category. Finally, the paper discusses the impact of variable network conditions on inference performance, which falls under the networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) category.
